review_blob: Great on ice. Had it on tap at The Empress Ale House in Edmonton. Crisp flavour, taste like real apples compared too other ciders. The color is deep orange. Very refreshing.
Had it on tap. Good wheat beer. Mild and fruity taste. The color is orange with uniform cloudiness, and large head. I can see why its popular at Octoberfest.
Great introductory craft beer. Good appearance, burnt orange color. Enjoyed the taste, not as hoppy as it sounds.
